<div id="site-wrap">
 
  <h1>FAQ</h1>

  <dl>
    <dt>What do I need to do to set up a website for my charity?</dt>
      <dd>To set up a charity in our system, you'll need a valid, government recognised charity number.</dd>
    <dt>How do I obtain a registered charity number?</dt>
      <dd>An application form for a charity tax exemption for your organisation must be made to the Revenue office. The form can be found <a href="http://www.revenue.ie/en/tax/it/leaflets/chy1.pdf">here</a>. Further information on registering charities can be found <a href="http://www.revenue.ie/en/business/faqs-charities.html#section1">here</a>.</dd>
    <dt>How do I donate to a charity?</dt>
      <dd>Donation pages can be found on a charity's page. A valid credit/debit card is required. Donations are processed using Stripe.</dd>
    <dt>How do I find a charity?</dt>
      <dd>Charities can be found by using the search box at the top of every page.</dd>
    <dt>Can I set up a charity site for any cause?</dt>
      <dd>You can only set up charity sites for animal related causes. A fund for helping abandoned animals, preservation of endangered species or lost and found articles for missing pets.</dd>
    <dt>How do I set up a lost and found page?</dt>
      <dd>Lost and found pages are hosted by specific charities. You can request a lost and found page by filling out a form on a participating charity's site.</dd>
    <dt>I no longer want to a charity website. How can I have it removed?</dt>
      <dd>There is an option to remove created charity websites in the control panel.</dd>
  </dl>
</div>